#: ../../C/core.rst:5
msgid "core"
msgstr "core"

#: ../../C/core.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../C/core.rst:9
msgid ""
"Main storage or RAM. Dates from the days of ferrite-core memory; now archaic"
" as techspeak most places outside IBM, but also still used in the Unix "
"community and by old-time hackers or those who would sound like them. Some "
"derived idioms are quite current; in core, for example, means ‘in memory’ "
"(as opposed to ‘on disk’), and both :ref:`core-dump` and the core image or "
"core file produced by one are terms in favor. Some varieties of Commonwealth"
" hackish prefer :ref:`store`\\."
msgstr ""
"主記憶またはRAM。フェライトコアメモリの時代に由来します。今やIBM以外のほとんどの場所では専門用語としては古風ですが、Unixコミュニティや古参のハッカー、あるいは彼らのように聞こえたい人々の間では今も使われています。派生した慣用句のいくつかはかなり現役です。たとえばin"
" coreは‘メモリ内’を意味し(‘ディスク上’に対して)、\\ :ref:`core-dump`\\ も、それによって生み出されるcore "
"imageやcore fileも好まれる用語です。一部の英連邦ハッカー用語の変種では\\ :ref:`store`\\ を好みます。"
